<!-- vraag_02 -->
    <div id="vraag_02" style="position: absolute; transform: translate(-50%, -50%) translate3d(26000px, -1500px, 0px) rotateX(0deg) rotateY(0deg) rotateZ(0deg) scale(1); transform-style: preserve-3d; "  class="step slide past" data-x="900000" data-y="-1500">

     <div style="width: 90%;  position: absolute; top: 20px; text-align:center;"><p style="font-size:200%;">Vraag 2</p><p style="font-size:100%; position:relative; top:20px;"></p></div>

<div style="position: absolute; top: 200px; left:100px; text-align:left; font-size:100%;">

<p>Which of the following provides a non-graphical, text based interface for users who are visually impaired
that can be used as a screen reader?</p><br>
<ul>
<li style="list-style:disc;">easyspeech</li>
<li style="list-style:disc;">textconvert</li>
<li style="list-style:disc;">xscreen</li>
<li style="list-style:disc;">emacspeak</li>
</ul>

</div>

